The Know Your Rights app is now available on Google Play for Android users. Photo: Sourced. Rhodes law alumna Michelle du Toit recently launched the Know Your Rights app. Available on the Google Play Store; the app serves as a way for South Africans to better understand the Bill of Rights. The app makes this information available in the 11 official languages, and soon will feature a read-aloud option for easier use. Currently the app is available for free to Android users, while access to iOS users is in the works.